div.bibl: Svenska Kuriren, Jan. 26, 1907. THE MAYORAL ELECTION IN CHICAGO

body.p: Carter H. Harrison, at present in California, has in a letter to his friends here withdrawn his candidacy for mayor in Chicago. It, there-fore, seems apparent that if Mr. Dunne is nominated, the Republican party will be forced to out forth its strongest candidate. No Republican can be elected this time in Chicago except Fred A. Busse, in the opinion of this paper.
